After vagrant provision, wait until the compilation is done.

You can see the compilations process:
$ vagrant ssh
$ sudo screen -r

Once it is done, run the following commands inside the vagrant box:
$ sudo -i
# cd /opt/mapnik-2.0.0/
# python scons/scons.py install
# fpm -s dir -n mapnik -v 2.0.0 --iteration $(read -p 'Release number: ' num; echo $num) -C /opt/mapnik-install/ -t rpm --prefix /usr --url http://mapnik.org/ --description "Mapnik is a Free Toolkit for developing mapping applications."

You will be prompted for a Release number. It is the release number of the RPM.

Your rpm is /opt/mapnik-2.0.0/mapnik-2.0.0-$RELEASE.x86_64.rpm

